Title: Coming Out Ball
Plot: When 18-year-old debutante Barbara Linden-Warner disappeared without trace 27 years ago, the assumption at the time was that she had been kidnapped and her father, a wealthy British arms manufacturer, paid a ransom for her return. When new evidence emerges about her last movements, the indication is that she may still be alive.
ParentalRatingReason: Lightbox Provisional Classification. Official NZ Rating To Be Confirmed.
